00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:31.470
Because people would panic.

00:39:31.470 --> 00:39:35.250
Surely some people would
panic and get upset.

00:39:35.250 --> 00:39:38.280
Do you trust the general
public with this information?

00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:40.800
- Yeah, actually, let's
start with that piece of it.

00:39:40.800 --> 00:39:42.870
And the social
scientists have done

00:39:42.870 --> 00:39:46.530
a number of research protocols.

00:39:46.530 --> 00:39:48.840
And they've asked the question.

00:39:48.840 --> 00:39:52.800
And they find that already,
an overwhelming percentage

00:39:52.800 --> 00:39:57.784
of the people on the planet
feel that it's quite likely

00:39:57.784 --> 00:39:58.950
that there's life out there.

00:39:58.950 --> 00:40:01.680
Some of them feel it's visited
us already, some of them.

00:40:01.680 --> 00:40:04.020
But it's not new news.

00:40:04.020 --> 00:40:06.860
It's really not the
kind of news for which

00:40:06.860 --> 00:40:09.490
you would panic at this point.

00:40:09.490 --> 00:40:14.180
This idea has seeped
out into the culture

00:40:14.180 --> 00:40:16.950
enough so that we don't
really think that there's

00:40:16.950 --> 00:40:18.240
an opportunity for panic.

00:40:18.240 --> 00:40:21.930
As to whether the government
would try and shut it down,

00:40:21.930 --> 00:40:26.230
it's really going to be a hell
of a difficult secret to keep.

00:40:26.230 --> 00:40:27.120
We are privately--

00:40:27.120 --> 00:40:28.260
