00:59:27.650 --> 00:59:31.560
a reception instead of lunch.

00:59:31.560 --> 00:59:34.460
And I would just
like to say thank you

00:59:34.460 --> 00:59:37.814
all for coming and for making
this such a fantastic day.

00:59:37.814 --> 00:59:39.230
And let me turn
it over to Caylee.

00:59:39.230 --> 00:59:40.198
Thank you.

00:59:40.198 --> 00:59:42.618
[APPLAUSE]

00:59:48.910 --> 00:59:50.250
- You all ready for round two?

00:59:50.250 --> 00:59:56.340
[LAUGHS] So I hope
that, because of all

00:59:56.340 --> 00:59:58.560
of these amazing speakers
we've had here today,

00:59:58.560 --> 01:00:01.860
that you can recontextualize
this poem I've written

01:00:01.860 --> 01:00:04.860
and have a much
deeper understanding

01:00:04.860 --> 01:00:07.110
of the meaning behind it.

01:00:07.110 --> 01:00:09.710
So in case you missed
it the first time,

01:00:09.710 --> 01:00:14.330
the poem's title is
"Method Versus Muse."

01:00:14.330 --> 01:00:18.530
"People have drawn a thick
line between art and science.

01:00:18.530 --> 01:00:21.890
But what is science
without the arts?

01:00:21.890 --> 01:00:23.750
The questions that
need to be asked

01:00:23.750 --> 01:00:26.660
can't come from a formula,
when, for centuries, they've

01:00:26.660 --> 01:00:30.950
been deeply rooted in the
hearts of geniuses and prophets

01:00:30.950 --> 01:00:33.230
with brains full of thought.

01:00:33.230 --> 01:00:35.360
It seems that,
over time, humanity

01:00:35.360 --> 01:00:40.170
forgot how to think critically
and to question with care.

01:00:40.170 --> 01:00:42.230
And in an age of
internet access,

01:00:42.230 --> 01:00:45.260
the answers are
always right there.

01:00:45.260 --> 01:00:47.840
And schools are so
focused on students

01:00:47.840 --> 01:00:49.610
having all the right
answers that they

01:00:49.610 --> 01:00:55.370
forget that we're poets,
and designers, and dancers.

01:00:55.370 --> 01:00:59.870
They draw facts on young minds
like piles of heavy bricks

01:00:59.870 --> 01:01:02.570
and expect us to
absorb information

01:01:02.570 --> 01:01:04.870
stacked miles thick.

01:01:04.870 --> 01:01:07.790
They teach us so much.

01:01:07.790 --> 01:01:10.640
But now, we need
to build from it.

01:01:10.640 --> 01:01:12.440
They marched with
us to base camp.

01:01:12.440 --> 01:01:14.900
But our goals are at the summit.

01:01:14.900 --> 01:01:18.170
Applying what we know to
explore the unforeseen

01:01:18.170 --> 01:01:20.750
and the undiscovered
is easier said

01:01:20.750 --> 01:01:24.380
than done when curiosities
lie dormant and smothered.

01:01:24.380 --> 01:01:28.340
Every day I see young minds
afraid to ask questions.

01:01:28.340 --> 01:01:33.660
It cripples the scientific
world at its very foundation.

01:01:33.660 --> 01:01:39.180
Research never comes without
curiosity, without a spark.

01:01:39.180 --> 01:01:41.790
And my spark would
have died too,

01:01:41.790 --> 01:01:44.340
but I found my
light in the dark.

01:01:44.340 --> 01:01:48.110
My creativity led me to
ask all the right things.

01:01:48.110 --> 01:01:51.690
And now I stand here before
you to ask, when will you

01:01:51.690 --> 01:01:55.010
change the tune that you sing?

01:01:55.010 --> 01:01:57.950
What will it take for
schools to open their eyes

01:01:57.950 --> 01:02:00.500
to a world of
unmatched opportunity

01:02:00.500 --> 01:02:03.740
that very clearly lies in
the minds of young people

01:02:03.740 --> 01:02:05.960
who still have their fire?

01:02:05.960 --> 01:02:08.240
When will you take
their thoughts

01:02:08.240 --> 01:02:10.490
and lift them up higher?

01:02:10.490 --> 01:02:13.040
Maybe you will be
the one to inspire

01:02:13.040 --> 01:02:17.600
someone's great questions
or someone's desire.

01:02:17.600 --> 01:02:22.070
Teach young minds to fall
in love with the unknown.

01:02:22.070 --> 01:02:25.970
For every question we ask,
there are many more to go.

01:02:25.970 --> 01:02:30.140
Nurture the creativity we
all harbor in our hearts.

01:02:30.140 --> 01:02:34.490
And maybe we will give way for
a new way of thinking to start."

01:02:34.490 --> 01:02:35.360
Thank you.

01:02:35.360 --> 01:02:37.460
[APPLAUSE]

01:02:42.260 --> 01:02:44.060
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:02:44.660 --> 01:02:46.460
- Thank you.

01:02:46.460 --> 01:02:48.910
Thank you so much.

